Apple today unveiled an update coming to <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/carplay/">CarPlay</a>, which will support the company's new "Liquid Glass" design to align with updates coming to <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ios-19/">iOS 26</a> later this year.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/06/f-92d82b76bfe8ca00151ab0403267ae79e768b966.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="900" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1004957" /><br/>
New features include the ability to quickly send Tapbacks in Messages, as well as support for <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/home-screen/">Widgets</a> and Live Activities. All of these updates are also coming to &zwnj;CarPlay&zwnj; Ultra.<br/>
